"HelpContent" : "The Access page can be reached by clicking Specify Access Control in the left panel of the Software Management page. This page allows you to specify the users and user groups that should have access to a selected package. There are two categories of user group package privileges: View and deploy the package Delete the package once it is published If you do not grant access for any users or user groups to a package privilege, only you (the creator of the package) and the system administrator will have that privilege.This page displays the name of the currently selected package with the following information: Package Description ? The description of the selected package. For example, in the above figure, the selected package is ?AcmePackage?. Package Version ? The version of the selected package, along with a lock icon that indicates whether or not the package has been published. If the package has not been published, the lock icon is red. If the package was published, the lock icon is green. Expiration ? The expiration date of the package, if the package has been set to expire. Selecting a Package to Specify AccessThe package that appears in this page is the last package that was created or selected in the Find Packages page. To select a different package: Click the Switch Package icon. The Find packages page appears. Filter the list (if necessary) and select the package to be tested by clicking on the package. Once the package is selected, the package name appears in the left panel of the Software Management application to indicate that it is selected. Click Specify Access Control in the left panel to return to the Access page. Confirm that the name of the selected package appears in the Selected Package field. Specifying Package AccessYou can select users and/or user groups that should have privileges to view and deploy, or delete the selected package once it is published. Use the Select User or Select User Group fields to search for and select a user or user group, respectively. Use the coordinating Select Access Control drop-down menus to select the privilege that the selected user or user group should have: View & Deploy ? The user or members of the user group can view and deploy the selected package. Delete ? The user or members of the user group can delete the selected package once it is published. Click the plus sign icon. The selected user or user group appears in the list below, with the assigned access privilege. Repeat the above steps as needed. Click Next to Publish the Package. Removing an Access AssignmentTo remove an access assignment from a user or user group, select the entry in the list, and then click the trash can above the list.You can also click Clear to remove all access assignments from the selected package.
